description:
Federal judges in Alexandria, Virginia, have lashed out at the Justice Department as they continue to list Lindsey Halligan on court documents — some going as far as striking her name from paperwork from the bench.

Two magistrate judges and a district court judge in Alexandria, Virginia, told prosecutors in open court they didn’t believe Halligan’s name should be on new criminal case filings, such as guilty plea documents and indictments, after a decision in the district last week said she is not the US Attorney.          #CNN #News
title: Judges lash out at Justice Department for still listing Lindsey Halligan on court documents

author: CNN
description:
Parkinson’s disease afflicts almost 12 million people worldwide. And the number of new cases is growing quickly. For roughly 13% of patients, genetics plays a key role. For many others, the underlying cause of the disease might be more mundane and insidious: environmental toxins. Neurologist Dr Michael Okun, co-author of The Parkinson’s Plan, joins CNN Chief Medical Correspondent Dr. Sanjay Gupta to discuss where we stand today in our understanding of this disease, and the “PLAN” moving forward.

Listen to the full episode on CNN's Chasing Life podcast: https://swap.fm/l/clytb120425

#cnn #news #health #medicine #parkinsons #parkinson #parkinsondisease #parkinsonsdisease #parkinsonscommunity #parkinsonstreatment #sanjaygupta #drsanjaygupta
title: A new understanding of Parkinson’s disease | Chasing Life

description: In Chemmani, northern Sri Lanka, a mass grave uncovered earlier this year is forcing a nation to confront the darkest chapters of its past. CNN’s Hanako Montgomery has more.
title: Sri Lanka’s bloody past revealed in mass graves
